=Description=

"The interaction of national and global organizing structures is increasingly affecting the coordination of economic, social and political activity in modern economies. In this blog, a group of researchers shares ideas, concepts and examples on how to deal with old and new forms of such transnational governance.

Mostly, we are are members and affiliates of the research group “Institution Building Across Borders” at Max Planck Institute for the Study of Societies in Cologne."


